sec.p:
There was a significant effect of time on both the SIAS and SPS
(F = 80.95 −83.39;
df = 2, p<.001). Mixed effects
model analysis showed no significant interaction of group and time for these
variables (F = 0.30–0.48;
df = 2, 244;
p = .62–.74).

There was a significant effect of time on MADRS-S, BAI, ASI and QOLI
(F = 17.26–52.30;
df = 2, 227–245; p<.001).
Analysis using mixed effects model yielded no significant interaction of
group and time for these variables
(F = 0.26–1.30;
df = 2, 227–245;
p = .28–.77).
